16/10/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia â Visiting US National Guard chief Lieutenant General Steven Blum reaffirmed US and NATO interest in co-operation with the Serbian military. 
During talks Friday (October 13th) with Serbian army deputy chief General Major Zdravko Ponos, Blum stressed that his country would like to see the establishment of a professional army in Serbia. 
He and Ponos described military collaboration between the two countries as at its highest level ever. 
(Danas - 14/10/06; Tanjug - 13/10/06)
